        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_B_001",
          "text": "The present age of a father is 3 times his son's age. In 12 years, the father will be twice the son's age. The son's present age is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "10 years",
            "b": "12 years",
            "c": "14 years",
            "d": "16 years"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Let son = x. Father = 3x. In 12 years: 3x+12 = 2(x+12) → 3x+12 = 2x+24 → x = 12."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_B_002",
          "text": "A fraction equals 2/3. If 4 is added to both numerator and denominator, the new fraction equals 3/4. The original numerator is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "8",
            "b": "10",
            "c": "12",
            "d": "16"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Let fraction = 2k/3k. (2k+4)/(3k+4) = 3/4 → 4(2k+4) = 3(3k+4) → 8k+16 = 9k+12 → k = 4. Original numerator = 2k = 8. Fraction = 8/12 = 2/3 ✓. After adding 4: 12/16 = 3/4 ✓."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_B_003",
          "text": "A sum of ₹700 is divided between A and B so that A gets ₹100 more than B. How much does B get?",
