          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "Complementary angles sum to 90°. Let angles be x and x+18. x + x+18 = 90 → 2x = 72 → x = 36. Larger = 54°."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_B_006",
          "text": "Raju has ₹x. He spends ₹250 on books and ₹180 on food. He is left with 1/3 of his original amount. What was his original amount?",
          "options": {
            "a": "₹585",
            "b": "₹615",
