        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_B_007",
          "text": "A train is travelling at 72 km/h. A man in the train walks at 3 km/h in the direction of the train. The speed of the man relative to the ground is: If this speed represents (5x + 5) km/h, the value of x is:",
