        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_C_001",
          "text": "A man is 4 times as old as his son. After 16 years, the man will be only twice as old. The man's present age is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "24 years",
            "b": "28 years",
            "c": "32 years",
            "d": "36 years"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Let son = x. Man = 4x. 4x+16 = 2(x+16) → 4x+16 = 2x+32 → 2x = 16 → x = 8. Man = 4×8 = 32 years."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_C_002",
          "text": "A two-digit number is 4 times the sum of its digits. If 18 is added to the number, the digits are reversed. The original number is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "24",
            "b": "36",
            "c": "48",
            "d": "60"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Let tens=t, units=u. Number=10t+u. 10t+u=4(t+u) → 6t=3u → u=2t. Reversed: 10u+t = 10t+u+18 → 9u-9t=18 → u-t=2. Sub u=2t: 2t-t=2 → t=2, u=4. Number=24. Verify: 24=4(2+4)=24 ✓. 24+18=42 (reversed) ✓."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_C_003",
          "text": "Rahim has some ₹50 notes and some ₹100 notes. He has 20 notes in total worth ₹1500. How many ₹100 notes does he have?",
          "options": {
            "a": "5",
            "b": "7",
            "c": "10",
            "d": "12"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "mp_birla",
          "explanation": "Let ₹100 notes = x. ₹50 notes = 20-x. 100x + 50(20-x) = 1500 → 100x + 1000 - 50x = 1500 → 50x = 500 → x = 10."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_C_004",
          "text": "A steamer goes downstream from A to B in 4 hours and upstream from B to A in 6 hours. If the stream's speed is 2 km/h, the distance AB is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "36 km",
            "b": "42 km",
            "c": "48 km",
            "d": "54 km"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Let speed in still water = v. Downstream = v+2, upstream = v-2. Distance = 4(v+2) = 6(v-2) → 4v+8 = 6v-12 → 20 = 2v → v = 10 km/h. Distance = 4×12 = 48 km."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_C_005",
          "text": "Divide 54 into two parts such that one part is 2/7 of the other. The smaller part is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "10",
            "b": "12",
            "c": "14",
            "d": "16"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Let larger part = x. Smaller = 2x/7. x + 2x/7 = 54 → 9x/7 = 54 → x = 42. Smaller = 2×42/7 = 12."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_C_006",
          "text": "In an examination, a student scores 4 marks for every correct answer and loses 1 mark for every wrong answer. He attempts 60 questions and scores 130 marks. How many questions did he answer correctly?",
          "options": {
            "a": "34",
            "b": "36",
            "c": "38",
            "d": "40"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "mp_birla",
          "explanation": "Let correct answers = x. Wrong = 60-x. 4x - 1(60-x) = 130 → 4x - 60 + x = 130 → 5x = 190 → x = 38. Verify: 4(38) - 1(22) = 152 - 22 = 130 ✓."
        }
      ]
    },
