          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Let tens digit = x. Units digit = 9-x. Original = 10x+(9-x) = 9x+9. Reversed = 10(9-x)+x = 90-9x. 9x+9-(90-9x) = 27 → 18x-81 = 27 → 18x = 108 → x = 6. Number = 63."
