          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Let p/q be the fraction. (p+1)/(q+1)=1/2 → q=2p+1. (p+3)/(q+3)=3/5 → 5(p+3)=3(q+3) → 5p+15=3(2p+1)+9=6p+12 → p=3. Numerator=3. Fraction=3/7."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch02_D_005",
          "text": "The present ages of A and B are in ratio 5:3. After 6 years, their ages will be in ratio 7:5. What is A's present age (in years)?",
          "correct_answer": "15",
